The fix is to enable SSL in the .env file. I can either:1. Set `NODE_ENV=production` (but this might have other side effects)
2. Add SSL configuration explicitly by modifying the code to always use SSL for Railway databases3. Update the .env to include SSL settings

The easiest and safest fix is to update the backend .env to enable SSL for Railway database connections. I should set SSL to require for Railway connections regardless of NODE_ENV.

